    "keywords" -> {"fermionic quantum computation"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiState[{nrm, cvr}] represents a fermionic Gaussian state with \
covariance matrix cvr in the Majorana spinor space and trace nrm (i.e., norm \
square in the case of pure state). BravyiState[{n1, n2, ...}, m] returns a \
BravyiState object corresponding to the computational basis state Ket[{n1, \
n2, ...}] of m fermion modes. If the list of occupation numbers {n1, n2, ...} \
is shorter (or longer) than m, then the occupation numbers are cyclically \
repeated (or the list is simply cut).", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "BravyiState", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "BravyiState", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiState"}},
